latestIgtvVideos.caption:
[BTS]

This concept has been running in my mind for the past 6 months. I have been reading about the artform and art since then. I have always known “theyyam” witnessed only an artist but not the dance once in my life. It scared me so much that I believed for a fact that I would be haunted by the “theyyam” god if I did not worship him.
It was extremely difficult to do this mentally and physically. Hoping to have opened the eyes of many like me to the unbelievable word of rebellion through art.
-
I have to thank my sister @rashmita_thampi for waking up in the middle of the night and capturing everything I asked her to do and more very patiently. Ily ♥️
-

Disclaimer: I am not a Theyyam artist. And the makeup, attire and form are not perfect depictions of the art and only an imitation of it. I admire and respect the art form and have tried to do my best to replicate the essence of it. This post is also in noway talking about my personal experience rather my way of sharing the knowledge about the concept. In this video, I am just being myself and not mocking the art.
-
Thanks for all the appreciation. I am beyond overwhelmed. 
-
#halloweenmakeup #halloween2021

🌼✨Happy Vijayadashami Loves✨🌼
-
As a child, Vijayadashami was always celebrated as the day Devi came home and I spent most of my day studying, singing and dancing in front of the deity. We used to also attempt a kolam at our apartment’s door front and keep the home spic and span for ‘Devi’.

Let’s say I encapsulated the vision of my Devi in an image. Or maybe Mukuthi Amman and kolamaavu Kokila in one look. 
-
The art of kolam has always intrigued me and I have made multiple attempts to perfect it at least on paper. Today, I proved myself that I can do it. Now I just need to learn how to do it with “kolamaavu” 💀
-
I had a completely different vision of this look in the beginning but after seeing @vvnloll ‘a Halloween day 13 look I changed my mind!

latestPosts.caption:
Recently, I went as a hair model for a friend — the first time since giving birth that I did something so simple, so mindless… just sit, breathe, and exist outside of being ‘mom.’ The mom guilt hit me like a wave, but my amazing family didn’t hesitate. The moment I asked, they stepped in to care for my daughter with so much love.

Even in the chaos, I know how blessed I am — to have this support, and to be surrounded by my girls at work who not only show up for me but hold me together. On the days I forget my body is still healing, they remind me with gentle care and quiet strength to slow down and be kind to myself.

#postpartum #momlife #infantmom #girlmom
